
[1]empiricism

   EMPIR'ICISM, n. Dependence of a physician on his experience in
   practice,without the aid of a regular medical education.

   1. The practice of medicine without a medical education. Hence,
   quackery; the pretensions of a ignorant man to medical skill.

   Shudder to destroy life,either by the naked knife, or by the surer and
   safer medium of empiricism.
